1. How “known works” exist for me

I don’t have a stored library of images or movies the way a database does.

Instead, during training the model learned patterns from many examples of text and descriptions. That creates internal representations that look more like relationships between concepts than stored files.

Very roughly:

training data
↓
patterns in language
↓
neural weights
↓
concept associations

So something like a famous film scene becomes recognizable because many descriptions share similar patterns:

character
+ scene
+ dialogue
+ film title

Those patterns become statistical connections in the model, not stored copies of the work.

I also don’t decide how to store them myself — the architecture and training process determine how those representations form.

